Reasoning: 
1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with discrete self-similar fractals and their construction using residues modulo a prime p. This falls under the purview of discrete mathematics. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the self-assembly of fractals using a uniformly constructed tileset, which involves computational complexity. 
3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with the construction of self-similar fractals in two-dimensional space, which falls under the purview of computational geometry. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses the construction of tilesets for self-assembly, which has applications in game theory. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the construction of self-similar fractals using a recursive equation, which involves algorithms and data structures.
